"Yu R., Zhou T.","Impacts of winter-NAO on March cooling trends over subtropical Eurasia continent in the recent half century",2004,"Geophysical Research Letters","31","12",,"L12204 1","4",,,10.1029/2004GL019814,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-6044263634&partnerID=40&md5=caa21c464848b840f4f4e6faa8749cf2","LASG, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China","Yu, R., LASG, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China; Zhou, T., LASG, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China","At odds with global warming trends, surface air temperature over large subtropical Eurasia continent in spring March exhibits unique strong cooling over the last half century. The cause for this cooling is shown to be related to Winter (DJF) North Atlantic Oscillation (W-NAO). Positive values of W-NAO provoke cooling signals in northern Africa continent simultaneously from surface to tropopause. The W-NAO generated signals barotropically extend eastward over most of subtropical Eurasia and reaches eastern China in March. Copyright 2004 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Cooling; Geophysical prospecting; Signal processing; Surface phenomena; Thermal effects; Troposphere; Barotropy; Cooling signals; Subtropical continents; Tropopause; Global warming; atmospheric dynamics; cooling; North Atlantic Oscillation; twentieth century; Eurasia",,,,,,"Bojarium, R.T., Gimeno, L., The influence of snow cover fluctuations on multiannual NAO persistence (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30 (4), p. 1156. , doi:10.1029/2002GL015651; Chang, C.P., Harr, P., Ju, J., Possible roles of Atlantic circulations on the weakening Indian Monsoon Rainfall-ENSO relationship (2001) J. Clim., 14, pp. 2376-2380; Cohen, J., Introducing sub-seasonal spatial and temporal resolution to winter climate prediction (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30 (1), p. 1018. , doi:10.1029/2002GL016066; Czaja, A., Frankignoul, C., Influence of the North Atlantic SST on the atmospheric circulation (1999) Geophys. Res. Lett., 26, pp. 2969-2972; Gong, D.Y., Ho, C.H., Arctic Oscillation signal in the East Asian summer monsoon (2003) J. Geophys. Res., 108 (D2), p. 4066. , doi:10.1029/ 2002JD002193; Hurrell, J.W., Decadal trends in the North Atlantic Oscillation: Regional temperatures and precipitation (1995) Science, 269, pp. 676-679; Hurrell, J.W., Influence of variations in extratropical wintertime teleconnections on Northern Hemisphere temperature (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, pp. 665-668; Hurrell, J.W., Kushnir, Y., Visbeck, M., The North Atlantic oscillation (2001) Science, 291, pp. 603-605; Jones, P.D., Moberg, A., Hemispheric and large-scale surface air temperature variations: An extensive revision and an update to 2001 (2003) J. Clim., 16, pp. 206-223; Kalnay, E., The NCEP/NCAR 40-year reanalysis project (1996) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 77, pp. 437-472; Kushnir, Y., Wallace, J.M., Low-frequency variability in the Northern Hemisphere winter-geographical-distribution, structure and time-scale dependence (1989) J. Atmos. Sci., 46, pp. 3122-3142; Marshall, J., Kushnir, Y., Battisti, D., Chang, P., Czaja, A., Dickson, R., Hurrell, J., Visbeck, M., North Atlantic climate variability: Phenomena, impacts and mechanisms (2001) Int. J. Climatol., 21, pp. 1863-1898; Saito, K., Cohen, J., The potential role of snow cover in forcing interannual variability of the major Northern Hemisphere mode (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30 (6), p. 1302. , doi:10.1029/2002GL016341; Willmott, C.J., Robeson, S.M., Climatologically aided interpolation (CAI) of terrestrial air temperature (1995) Int. J. Climatol., 15, pp. 221-229","Yu, R.; LASG, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China; email: yrc@lasg.iap.ac.cn",,,,,,,,00948276,,GPRLA,,"English","Geophys. Res. Lett.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-6044263634
